Theft - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Twenty (20) days jail, imposed and stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion; 
2) Complete a mental health assessment;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Pay costs of action; 
5) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
6) Have no employment involving home health care or in the private setting;
7) Submit DNA sample.   
Minutes.
